snippet.textDisplay:
So, here’s why I don’t understand why some people loathe Jimmy Fallon:
I grew up watching The Carol Burnett Show. I watched the show every time it was on (I think it might have been in syndication already). The funniest thing about her show was not just the high comedic caliber writing, it was when the actors —Carol, Vicki, Tim, Steve, etc—would break character. They’d literally just flub up a line and then the laughter party started rolling most times-live!😂. THATis why I always loved Jimmy on SNL and then on his show. That guy could never keep it together, and there I’d be laughing out loud with him. Three are my favorites: The “whirlpool” sketch with Drew Barrymore, Rachel Dratch, and Will Ferrell, The “I need more Cowbell” both from SNL, and his uncut interview with Bradley Cooper on the Tonight Show (it was something about Cooper and The Elephant Man and they’re wearing those ridiculous hats). 😂. So yeah, I see I’ve written a book, but I just felt had to TRY to justify Jimmy as a person and personality. His laughter is real, and I’m fully assured so is his pain. ✌🏼💛💜

The funniest thing about her show was not just the high comedic caliber writing, it was when the actors —Carol, Vicki, Tim, Steve, etc—would break character. They’d literally just flub up a line and then the laughter party started rolling most times-live!😂. THATis why I always loved Jimmy on SNL and then on his show.  That guy could never keep it together, and there I’d be laughing out loud with him. Three are my favorites: The “whirlpool” sketch with Drew Barrymore, Rachel Dratch, and Will Ferrell, The “I need more Cowbell” both from SNL, and his uncut interview with Bradley Cooper on the Tonight Show (it was something about Cooper and The Elephant Man and they’re wearing those ridiculous hats). 😂.
